TITLE: Configuring Query Blocking with Per-Tenant Overrides in YAML
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use per-tenant overrides in Grafana Loki to block unwanted queries. It shows various blocking methods including exact matching, regex patterns, query type filtering, and hash-based blocking.
SOURCE: https://github.com/grafana/loki/blob/main/docs/sources/operations/blocking-queries.md#2025-04-19_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
overrides:
  "tenant-id":
    blocked_queries:
      # block this query exactly
      - pattern: 'sum(rate({env="prod"}[1m]))'

      # block any query matching this regex pattern 
      - pattern: '.*prod.*'
        regex: true

      # block all metric queries
      - types: metric

      # block any filter or limited queries matching this regex pattern 
      - pattern: '.*prod.*'
        regex: true
        types: filter,limited

      # block any query that matches this query hash
      - hash: 2943214005          # hash of {stream="stdout",pod="loki-canary-9w49x"}
        types: filter,limited
```

