TITLE: Basic Stream Compression with Zstd in Go
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to compress input from a reader to an output writer using zstd compression with default settings. The function creates a new zstd writer, copies data from input to the encoder, and properly closes the encoder when done.
SOURCE: https://github.com/grafana/loki/blob/main/vendor/github.com/klauspost/compress/zstd/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Go
CODE:
```
// Compress input to output.
func Compress(in io.Reader, out io.Writer) error {
    enc, err := zstd.NewWriter(out)
    if err != nil {
        return err
    }
    _, err = io.Copy(enc, in)
    if err != nil {
        enc.Close()
        return err
    }
    return enc.Close()
}
```

