TITLE: Implementing Basic LRU Cache in Go
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create and use a basic LRU cache with a fixed size of 128 elements. It adds 256 elements to the cache and verifies that the length remains at 128 due to the LRU eviction policy.
SOURCE: https://github.com/grafana/loki/blob/main/vendor/github.com/hashicorp/golang-lru/v2/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
package main

import (
	"fmt"
	"github.com/hashicorp/golang-lru/v2"
)

func main() {
	l, _ := lru.New[int, any](128)
	for i := 0; i < 256; i++ {
		l.Add(i, nil)
	}
	if l.Len() != 128 {
		panic(fmt.Sprintf("bad len: %v", l.Len()))
	}
}
```

