TITLE: Listing All Containers Using Docker Engine API Go Client
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use the Docker Engine API Go client to list all containers, equivalent to the 'docker ps --all' command. It initializes the API client, retrieves the container list, and prints the ID, image, and status of each container.
SOURCE: https://github.com/grafana/loki/blob/main/vendor/github.com/docker/docker/client/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
package main

import (
	"context"
	"fmt"

	"github.com/docker/docker/api/types/container"
	"github.com/docker/docker/client"
)

func main() {
	apiClient, err := client.NewClientWithOpts(client.FromEnv)
	if err != nil {
		panic(err)
	}
	defer apiClient.Close()

	containers, err := apiClient.ContainerList(context.Background(), container.ListOptions{All: true})
	if err != nil {
		panic(err)
	}

	for _, ctr := range containers {
		fmt.Printf("%s %s (status: %s)\n", ctr.ID, ctr.Image, ctr.Status)
	}
}
```

