TITLE: Publishing and Subscribing to Google Cloud Pub/Sub in Go
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to publish a message to a Pub/Sub topic and receive messages via a subscription. It demonstrates asynchronous publishing with result handling and message acknowledgment when consuming messages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/grafana/loki/blob/main/vendor/cloud.google.com/go/pubsub/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
// Publish "hello world" on topic1.
topic := client.Topic("topic1")
res := topic.Publish(ctx, &pubsub.Message{
	Data: []byte("hello world"),
})
// The publish happens asynchronously.
// Later, you can get the result from res:
...
msgID, err := res.Get(ctx)
if err != nil {
	log.Fatal(err)
}

// Use a callback to receive messages via subscription1.
sub := client.Subscription("subscription1")
err = sub.Receive(ctx, func(ctx context.Context, m *pubsub.Message) {
	fmt.Println(m.Data)
	m.Ack() // Acknowledge that we've consumed the message.
})
if err != nil {
	log.Println(err)
}
```

