TITLE: Implementing Streaming Decompression in Go with zstd
DESCRIPTION: Example of how to set up streaming decompression using the zstd library. This code creates a reader that decompresses zstd-compressed data from an input stream and writes it to an output stream, with proper resource cleanup through defer.
SOURCE: https://github.com/grafana/loki/blob/main/vendor/github.com/klauspost/compress/zstd/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
import "github.com/klauspost/compress/zstd"

func Decompress(in io.Reader, out io.Writer) error {
    d, err := zstd.NewReader(in)
    if err != nil {
        return err
    }
    defer d.Close()

    // Copy content...
    _, err = io.Copy(out, d)
    return err
}
```

