TITLE: Implementing OSC52 Clipboard Operations in Go
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use the go-osc52 library to perform various clipboard operations including copying to system clipboard, copying to primary clipboard (X11), querying the clipboard, clearing the clipboard, and using the fmt.Stringer interface.
SOURCE: https://github.com/grafana/loki/blob/main/vendor/github.com/aymanbagabas/go-osc52/v2/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
import (
  "os"
  "fmt"

  "github.com/aymanbagabas/go-osc52/v2"
)

func main() {
  s := "Hello World!"

  // Copy `s` to system clipboard
  osc52.New(s).WriteTo(os.Stderr)

  // Copy `s` to primary clipboard (X11)
  osc52.New(s).Primary().WriteTo(os.Stderr)

  // Query the clipboard
  osc52.Query().WriteTo(os.Stderr)

  // Clear system clipboard
  osc52.Clear().WriteTo(os.Stderr)

  // Use the fmt.Stringer interface to copy `s` to system clipboard
  fmt.Fprint(os.Stderr, osc52.New(s))

  // Or to primary clipboard
  fmt.Fprint(os.Stderr, osc52.New(s).Primary())
}
```

