TITLE: Marshaling and Unmarshaling YAML with Person Struct in Go
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to marshal a Person struct to YAML and then unmarshal it back into a struct using the sigs.k8s.io/yaml package. It showcases the use of JSON struct tags for YAML field naming.
SOURCE: https://github.com/grafana/loki/blob/main/vendor/sigs.k8s.io/yaml/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
package main

import (
	"fmt"

	"sigs.k8s.io/yaml"
)

type Person struct {
	Name string `json:"name"` // Affects YAML field names too.
	Age  int    `json:"age"`
}

func main() {
	// Marshal a Person struct to YAML.
	p := Person{"John", 30}
	y, err := yaml.Marshal(p)
	if err != nil {
		fmt.Printf("err: %v\n", err)
		return
	}
	fmt.Println(string(y))
	/* Output:
	age: 30
	name: John
	*/

	// Unmarshal the YAML back into a Person struct.
	var p2 Person
	err = yaml.Unmarshal(y, &p2)
	if err != nil {
		fmt.Printf("err: %v\n", err)
		return
	}
	fmt.Println(p2)
	/* Output:
	{John 30}
	*/
}
```

