TITLE: Advanced Redis Commands with Go-Redis
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates various advanced Redis commands using go-redis, including SetNX with TTL, Sort with options, ZRangeByScoreWithScores, ZInterStore with weights, Eval for Lua scripting, and custom commands using Do().
SOURCE: https://github.com/grafana/loki/blob/main/vendor/github.com/redis/go-redis/v9/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
// SET key value EX 10 NX
set, err := rdb.SetNX(ctx, "key", "value", 10*time.Second).Result()

// SET key value keepttl NX
set, err := rdb.SetNX(ctx, "key", "value", redis.KeepTTL).Result()

// SORT list LIMIT 0 2 ASC
vals, err := rdb.Sort(ctx, "list", &redis.Sort{Offset: 0, Count: 2, Order: "ASC"}).Result()

// ZRANGEBYSCORE zset -inf +inf WITHSCORES LIMIT 0 2
