TITLE: Implementing buffer reuse for JSON encoding
DESCRIPTION: Go code demonstrating how to implement buffer reuse using sync.Pool to improve encoding performance.
SOURCE: https://github.com/grafana/loki/blob/main/vendor/github.com/goccy/go-json/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
type buffer struct {
    data []byte
}

var bufPool = sync.Pool{
    New: func() interface{} {
        return &buffer{data: make([]byte, 0, 1024)}
    },
}

buf := bufPool.Get().(*buffer)
data := encode(buf.data) // reuse buf.data

newBuf := make([]byte, len(data))
copy(newBuf, buf)

buf.data = data
bufPool.Put(buf)
```

