TITLE: Implementing HTTP Backup Handler for Bolt Database in Go
DESCRIPTION: This code creates an HTTP handler function to backup a Bolt database. It sets appropriate headers for content type, filename, and length before writing the database content to the response writer. This enables hot backups without blocking other database operations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/grafana/loki/blob/main/vendor/go.etcd.io/bbolt/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_21

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
func BackupHandleFunc(w http.ResponseWriter, req *http.Request) {
	err := db.View(func(tx *bolt.Tx) error {
		w.Header().Set("Content-Type", "application/octet-stream")
		w.Header().Set("Content-Disposition", `attachment; filename="my.db"`)
		w.Header().Set("Content-Length", strconv.Itoa(int(tx.Size())))
		_, err := tx.WriteTo(w)
		return err
	})
	if err != nil {
		http.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)
	}
}
```

