TITLE: Implementing Option Pattern for Mock Clock in Go
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the recommended pattern for injecting a mock clock using the Option pattern, which keeps the production code clean while allowing easy testing.
SOURCE: https://github.com/grafana/loki/blob/main/vendor/github.com/coder/quartz/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
type Option func(*Thing)

// WithTestClock is used in tests to inject a mock Clock
func WithTestClock(clk quartz.Clock) Option {
	return func(t *Thing) {
		t.clock = clk
	}
}

func NewThing(<required args>, opts ...Option) *Thing {
	t := &Thing{
		...
		clock: quartz.NewReal()
	}
	for _, o := range opts {
	  o(t)
	}
	return t
}
```

