TITLE: Implementing Gzip Compression for HTTP Responses in Go
DESCRIPTION: Complete example showing how to wrap an HTTP handler with gzip compression functionality. The example demonstrates creating a basic handler that returns plain text and then wrapping it with GzipHandler to enable compression.
SOURCE: https://github.com/grafana/loki/blob/main/vendor/github.com/NYTimes/gziphandler/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
package main

import (
	"io"
	"net/http"
	"github.com/NYTimes/gziphandler"
)

func main() {
	withoutGz := http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
		w.Header().Set("Content-Type", "text/plain")
		io.WriteString(w, "Hello, World")
	})

	withGz := gziphandler.GzipHandler(withoutGz)

	http.Handle("/", withGz)
	http.ListenAndServe("0.0.0.0:8000", nil)
}
```

