TITLE: Finding Multiple Matches with regexp2 in Go
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of a function similar to regexp.FindAllString that finds all matches in a string using FindNextMatch method.
SOURCE: https://github.com/grafana/loki/blob/main/vendor/github.com/dlclark/regexp2/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
func regexp2FindAllString(re *regexp2.Regexp, s string) []string {
	var matches []string
	m, _ := re.FindStringMatch(s)
	for m != nil {
		matches = append(matches, m.String())
		m, _ = re.FindNextMatch(m)
	}
	return matches
}
```

