TITLE: Eliminating reflection in JSON encoding using type pointers
DESCRIPTION: Go code showing how to eliminate reflection in JSON encoding by using type pointers and pre-built optimized encoders.
SOURCE: https://github.com/grafana/loki/blob/main/vendor/github.com/goccy/go-json/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
type emptyInterface struct {
    typ unsafe.Pointer
    ptr unsafe.Pointer
}

var typeToEncoder = map[uintptr]func(unsafe.Pointer)([]byte, error){}

func Marshal(v interface{}) ([]byte, error) {
    iface := (*emptyInterface)(unsafe.Pointer(&v)
    typeptr := uintptr(iface.typ)
    if enc, exists := typeToEncoder[typeptr]; exists {
        return enc(iface.ptr)
    }
    ...
}
```

