TITLE: Configuring Promtail with Dynamic Labels for Apache Logs
DESCRIPTION: This YAML configuration demonstrates how to use regex-based pipeline stages in Promtail to dynamically set labels based on log content.
SOURCE: https://github.com/grafana/loki/blob/main/docs/sources/get-started/labels/_index.md#2025-04-19_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
- job_name: system
  pipeline_stages:
     - regex:
       expression: "^(?P<ip>\\S+) (?P<identd>\\S+) (?P<user>\\S+) \\[(?P<timestamp>[\\w:/]+\\s[+\\-]\\d{4})\\] \"(?P<action>\\S+)\\s?(?P<path>\\S+)?\\s?(?P<protocol>\\S+)?\" (?P<status_code>\\d{3}|-) (?P<size>\\d+|-)\\s?\"?(?P<referer>[^\"]*)\"?\\s?\"?(?P<useragent>[^\"]*)?\""
   - labels:
       action:
       status_code:
  static_configs:
  - targets:
     - localhost
    labels:
     job: apache
     env: dev
     __path__: /var/log/apache.log
```

