TITLE: Context-based Trace Nesting in Go
DESCRIPTION: Creates nested traces using context.Context to manage the trace hierarchy. This approach allows traces to be passed through function calls, enabling proper nesting even across different functions or packages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/grafana/loki/blob/main/vendor/k8s.io/utils/trace/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
func doSomething(ctx context.Context) {
    opTrace := trace.FromContext(ctx).Nest("operation") // create a trace, possibly nested
    ctx = trace.ContextWithTrace(ctx, opTrace) // make this trace the parent trace of the context
    defer opTrace.LogIfLong(50 * time.Millisecond)

    doSomethingElse(ctx)
}
```

